A custom implementation of {@link java.util.HashSet} in order To reduce memory consumption.
Profiling tests (Oct 2008) have shown that each element {@link FormulaCellCacheEntry} takes around 32 bytes To store in a HashSet, but around 6 bytes To store here. For Spreadsheets with thousands of formula cells with multiple interdependencies, the savings can be very significant.
